Below is the final integrated SysML v2 model, merging the StructuralDefinitions and BehavioralDefinitions packages into a single, coherent system. It links the control‐loop behavior and state machine to the Controller part, preserves all original elements, resolves types, and documents key integration assumptions.

```sysml
package IntegratedControlSystem {
    import StructuralDefinitions::*;
    import BehavioralDefinitions::*;

    doc /* Integrated control system combining structure and behavior */

    // Enhanced Controller with integrated control logic and state machine
    part def EnhancedController :> Controller {
        // Link the main control loop action into the controller
        perform controlLoop : ControlLoop;
        // Expose the system’s operational states on the controller
        exhibit states : SystemStates;
    }

    // Complete system assembly with behavioral integration
    part integratedSystem :> system {
        part controller : EnhancedController {
            :>> cycleTime = 0.1;  // 100 ms control cycle
        }
        part tempSensor : Sensor;
        part motor      : Actuator;

        // Physical/interface connections inherited from the structural model
        connect tempSensor.dataOut to controller.sensorIn;
        connect controller.actuatorOut to motor.commandIn;
    }
}

/* Integration Assumptions:
 * 1. ControlLoop executes continuously at the controller’s cycleTime rate.
 * 2. ReadSensor action reads from controller.sensorIn port.
 * 3. SendCommand action writes to controller.actuatorOut port.
 * 4. SystemStates transitions are triggered by ValidateInput results:
 *    – idle → active on system start
 *    – active → error when validate.valid = false
 *    – error → idle after error recovery
 * 5. Flow connections represent logical data/control flow
 *    while port connections represent physical/interface links.
 */
```

